==English==

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[innemest]]'', {{AS.}} ''[[innemest]]'', a double superlative form from ''[[inne]]'' within, from ''[[in]]'' in.  The modern form is due to confusion with most.

===Adjective===
'''inmost'''

# Deepest [[within]]; farthest from the surface or external part; [[innermost]].

